abstract: Bernie Sanders' surge to the front of the Democratic presidential contest has echoes of Donald Trump's improbable 2016 nomination, according to Republican strategists who tried and failed to stop the man who later won the presidency.
snippet: Bernie Sanders' surge to the front of the Democratic presidential contest has echoes of Donald Trump's improbable 2016 nomination, according to Republican strategists who tried and failed to stop the man who later won the presidency.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Bernie Sanders' surge to the front of the Democratic presidential contest has echoes of Donald Trump's improbable 2016 nomination, according to Republican strategists who tried and failed to stop the man who later won the presidency.
headline_main: Republicans See Echoes of Trump's Improbable Rise in Sanders' Surge
headline_print_headline: Republicans See Echoes of Trump's Improbable Rise in Sanders' Surge

abstract: Democratic presidential candidate Amy Klobuchar is “in very good health,” according to a medical report the Minnesota senator's campaign released days after she said during a debate over Bernie Sanders' health records that “you should release your records from your physical.”
snippet: Democratic presidential candidate Amy Klobuchar is “in very good health,” according to a medical report the Minnesota senator's campaign released days after she said during a debate over Bernie Sanders' health records that “you should release your...
lead_paragraph: CHICAGO — Democratic presidential candidate Amy Klobuchar is “in very good health,” according to a medical report the Minnesota senator's campaign released days after she said during a debate over Bernie Sanders' health records that “you should release your records from your physical.”
headline_main: Medical Report Shows Klobuchar in 'Very Good Health'
headline_print_headline: Medical Report Shows Klobuchar in 'Very Good Health'

abstract: The State newspaper in Columbia, South Carolina, has endorsed Pete Buttigieg for the Democratic Party presidential nomination ahead of Saturday's primary contest there, calling him the best candidate to unite Americans.
snippet: The State newspaper in Columbia, South Carolina, has endorsed Pete Buttigieg for the Democratic Party presidential nomination ahead of Saturday's primary contest there, calling him the best candidate to unite Americans.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - The State newspaper in Columbia, South Carolina, has endorsed Pete Buttigieg for the Democratic Party presidential nomination ahead of Saturday's primary contest there, calling him the best candidate to unite Americans.
headline_main: Buttigieg Wins Endorsement From South Carolina Newspaper
headline_print_headline: Buttigieg Wins Endorsement From South Carolina Newspaper

abstract: U.S. President Donald Trump said on Tuesday that no country was trying to help him win the November election, after a top intelligence official told lawmakers Russia was interfering in the 2020 presidential vote to help Trump win a second term.
snippet: U.S. President Donald Trump said on Tuesday that no country was trying to help him win the November election, after a top intelligence official told lawmakers Russia was interfering in the 2020 presidential vote to help Trump win a second term.
lead_paragraph: NEW DELHI — U.S. President Donald Trump said on Tuesday that no country was trying to help him win the November election, after a top intelligence official told lawmakers Russia was interfering in the 2020 presidential vote to help Trump win a second term.
headline_main: Trump: No Election Help Wanted or Received From Any Country
headline_print_headline: Trump: No Election Help Wanted or Received From Any Country

abstract: Without evidence, President Trump accused the chairman of the House Intelligence Committee of leaking intelligence.
snippet: Without evidence, President Trump accused the chairman of the House Intelligence Committee of leaking intelligence.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump on Tuesday accused Representative Adam B. Schiff, the chairman of the House Intelligence Committee, of leaking information about Russia’s efforts to interfere in the 2020 election, dismissed the intelligence as “exaggerated” and refused to acknowledge that Moscow was behind similar efforts in 2016.

abstract: Former U.S. Secretary of State Hillary Clinton has expressed her skepticism about Bernie Sanders but says she will support the Democratic nominee regardless of who it is.
snippet: Former U.S. Secretary of State Hillary Clinton has expressed her skepticism about Bernie Sanders but says she will support the Democratic nominee regardless of who it is.
lead_paragraph: BERLIN — Former U.S. Secretary of State Hillary Clinton has expressed her skepticism about Bernie Sanders but says she will support the Democratic nominee regardless of who it is.
headline_main: Hillary Clinton: Will Support Sanders if Nominated for Dems
headline_print_headline: Hillary Clinton: Will Support Sanders if Nominated for Dems

abstract: Surging Democratic presidential front-runner Bernie Sanders came under withering fire in a boisterous debate in South Carolina on Tuesday, as rivals attacked the high cost of his ambitious economic agenda and warned he would cost the party the White House and control of Congress.

lead_paragraph: CHARLESTON, S.C. — Surging Democratic presidential front-runner Bernie Sanders came under withering fire in a boisterous debate in South Carolina on Tuesday, as rivals attacked the high cost of his ambitious economic agenda and warned he would cost the party the White House and control of Congress.
headline_main: Rivals Question Front-Runner Sanders' Electability at Rowdy South Carolina Democratic Debate
headline_print_headline: Rivals Question Front-Runner Sanders' Electability at Rowdy South Carolina Democratic Debate
